<http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/9a03b4e4-0c98-4e6d-b360-da0c58ee1f3d> a skos:Concept ;
    dcterms:created "2025-06-25T08:34:37.873000+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    dcterms:modified "2025-06-26T11:01:28.310000+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    skos:broader <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/1263d9b4-76ce-4d59-82a7-94ef797b4b8f> ;
    skos:definition "Describes a situation in which the propagation of an initial impact is transmitted through a cascade of impacts on system components. Impacts at each tier of the cascade are themselves associated with a recipient risk of concern, the extent of which may be influenced by other features of the transmission dynamics. For example, businesses handling materials at different ‘stages’ of a complex supply chain (e.g., export, processing, retail), with disruptions at each stage having knock-on consequences e.g., for profitability for each recipient group (Carter et al., 2021)."@en ;
    skos:historyNote "Carter, T.R., Benzie, M., Campiglio, E., Carlsen, H., Franzek, S., Hildén, M., Reyer, C.P.O. and West, C. (2021). A conceptual framework for cross-border impacts of climate change. Global Environmental Change, 69, https://doi.org/10.1016/j.gloenvcha.2021.102307"@en ;
    skos:inScheme <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/> ;
    skos:narrower <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/5a02c7e5-d036-4ba0-9a00-6ee891f9fde5> ;
    skos:prefLabel "Cascade tiers"@en ;
    skos:related <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/0ae68762-fb7d-47e2-a0c8-3ff0ef9d8155>,
        <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/59a9d753-5ce4-489e-addb-715319eed174>,
        <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/ad0f0538-f168-4c67-afce-dc9598155cde>,
        <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/affa52fc-b12e-443d-8710-33250d80e9eb>,
        <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/f0914a46-c1d4-445d-b5fc-cf24218fb4fe> ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/> ;
    ns1:revisionNo 17 .

<http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/1263d9b4-76ce-4d59-82a7-94ef797b4b8f> a skos:Concept ;
    dcterms:created "2025-06-26T07:50:38.709000+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    dcterms:modified "2025-06-26T15:09:13.755000+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    skos:broader <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/0ae68762-fb7d-47e2-a0c8-3ff0ef9d8155> ;
    skos:definition "Cascading climate risk arises from a possibility of the initial climate impact triggering a further sequence of events, often across multiple systems and locations. This makes cascading risk a particular type of indirect risk, characterised specifically by a chain reaction of repercussions (Arrighi et al., 2021)."@en ;
    skos:historyNote """Arrighi, C., Pregnolato, M., and Castelli, F.: Indirect flood impacts and cascade risk across interdependent linear infrastructures, Nat. Hazards Earth Syst. Sci., 21, 1955–1969, https://doi.org/10.5194/nhess-21-1955-2021, 2021.

Bednar-Friedl, B., Knittel, N., Raich, J. and Adams, K.M. (2022). 'Adaptation to transboundary climate risks in trade: Investigating actors and strategies for an emerging challenge', WIRE's Climate Change, 13:e758, https://doi.org/10.1002/wcc.758 

Hochrainer-Stigler, S., Reiter, K. Risk-Layering for Indirect Effects. Int J Disaster Risk Sci 12, 770–778 (2021). https://doi.org/10.1007/s13753-021-00366-2"""@en ;
    skos:inScheme <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/> ;
    skos:narrower <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/9a03b4e4-0c98-4e6d-b360-da0c58ee1f3d> ;
    skos:prefLabel "Cascading climate risk"@en ;
    skos:related <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/25b337e4-3277-4a3e-87c9-0a8f6a657939>,
        <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/59a9d753-5ce4-489e-addb-715319eed174>,
        <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/5a02c7e5-d036-4ba0-9a00-6ee891f9fde5>,
        <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/a8b34fb2-6d75-4281-a527-f1764e3bb3f2>,
        <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/ad0f0538-f168-4c67-afce-dc9598155cde>,
        <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/f0914a46-c1d4-445d-b5fc-cf24218fb4fe> ;
    skos:scopeNote "Cascading climate risks, being a subset of indirect risks, invoke differences between first-order climate risks (e.g., direct climate risks, often contained within national borders) and higher-order risks (e.g., risks which are triggered elsewhere and may flow across sectors or borders). Risks conceptualised in this way may be plausibly contained within a national border, but across sectors, as the key characteristic is the hierarchical ordering of a risk, rather than the distance it flows (Bednar-Friedl et al., 2022)."@en ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/> ;
    ns1:revisionNo 21 .

<http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/2f2bf4de-7b28-49a6-a9a1-b3eb0ef0e9ef> a skos:Concept ;
    dcterms:created "2025-06-05T14:27:19.397000+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    dcterms:modified "2025-06-05T14:30:46.575000+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime,
        "2025-06-30T13:15:40.454000+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    skos:altLabel "complex system"@en,
        "complex systems"@en ;
    skos:definition "Systems characterized by complex interactions, where unexpected outcomes are more likely to occur. They differ from linear systems in that they have tight spacing of equipment, many common-mode connections, limited options for substitution of supplies and materials, and unfamiliar or unintended feedback loops (Aall et al., 2020)."@en ;
    skos:historyNote """Aall, C., Leander, E., Menk, L., Meyer, M., Dale, B., Lückerath, D., Nyadzi, E., Rome, E., Rudolf, F., Goosen, H., André, K.,Harris, K., Becker, L., Fulco, L., Benzie, M., Zebisch, M., Hanssen Korsbrekke, M., Jansen, M.K., Durmaz, N., Kienberger, S., Terzi, S., Lehr, U. & Gerger Swartling, Å. (2020). Methods for climate change risk assessments: An international knowledge review. Vestlandsforskingsrapport 7/2020. Sogndal: Western Norway Research Institute. Retrieved from https://www.vestforsk.no/
sites/default/files/2021-01/D1.1 knowledge%20review%20final2%20%281%29.pdf."""@en ;
    skos:inScheme <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/> ;
    skos:narrower <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/0b56c5c7-332e-4311-854e-688deb1cc52b>,
        <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/56d62584-ac5b-44f7-a293-e703d39a5a5b>,
        <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/5fb5574a-4ed4-473c-b099-2ad29a10ab08>,
